	(10039,113,'page_header','Homepage Conversion Rate'),
	(10040,113,'page_sub_header','Improved Conversion Rate of New Users on the Homepage by 25%'),
	(10041,113,'challenge_header','Challenge:'),
	(10042,113,'challenge_content','<p class=\"tb f5\"><span class=\"tx\">72% of new users dropped off (and never converted) after clicking</span><span class=\"tx f14\"> </span><span class=\"tx f910\">a prominent “Buy Now”</span><span class=\"tx f910\">button on our client’s homepage. Our challenge was to understand what was occurring and</span></p><p class=\"tb f5\"><span class=\"tx\">improve the drop off.</span></p>'),
	(10043,113,'solution_header','Solution:'),
	(10044,113,'solution_content','<p class=\"tb f5\"><span class=\"tx\">We analyzed user pathways in Analytics and determined the location of conversion </span><span class=\"tx f910\">“bottlenecking”. We devised a va</span><span class=\"tx\">riety of advanced site testing campaigns designed to reveal the </span>top performing conversion page(s). </p>'),
	(10045,113,'results_header','Results:'),
	(10046,113,'results_content','<p><span class=\"tx\">Through analysis and A/B site testing we were able improve conversion rate of new users </span><span class=\"tx f910\">clicking “Buy now” by 25%</span><span class=\"tx\"> and add-to-cart rate by 43%. The insights gained through landing </span><span class=\"tx\">page tests further benefit future optimization on the site and will fold into long term strategy for </span><span class=\"tx\">growing direct traffic sales. </span></p>'),
